Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the chicken from its packaging. Place @Slow Cooked British Chicken{290%g} in an #overproof dish{}, discarding the juices. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover loosely with #foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Next, spread the @McCain Home Chips{400%g} on a #baking tray{} in a single layer. Bake on the top shelf, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway.

Once cooked, remove the chicken from the oven. Shred as finely as you can.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure it's piping hot throughout.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in the @Chipotle Paste{20%g} and @BBQ Sauce{96%g}.

Microwave the @Plain Taco Tortillas{3.96} (2 per person) for 850W: ~{50%secs} / 750W: ~{1%min}.

> If you don't have a microwave, just enjoy them cold.

Pop the tortillas on your plates.

Top with the @Baby Leaf Mix{20%g}, pulled chicken, @Soured Cream{75%g} and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

Serve with the chips on the side.

Enjoy!